      
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Introduction to Histopathology</title>
    <meta name="description" content="This course provides a comprehensive introduction to the field of histopathology, covering the microscopic study of normal and diseased tissues. It explores various histological techniques, their applications in research and diagnosis, and the importance of histopathology in understanding diseases.">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/main.css">
</head>
<body>
    <article class="course-overview">
        <header class="course-header">
            <h1>Introduction to Histopathology</h1>
            <div class="course-meta">
                <span class="duration">Duration: 15 hours</span>
                <span class="level">Level: Intermediate</span>
            </div>
            <section class="course-intro">
                <h2>Course Overview</h2>
                <p>This course provides a comprehensive introduction to the field of histopathology, covering the microscopic study of normal and diseased tissues. It explores various histological techniques, their applications in research and diagnosis, and the importance of histopathology in understanding diseases.</p>
            </section>
            <section class="learning-path">
                <h2>🎯 Course Objectives</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Understand the fundamental principles of histology and histopathology.</li>
                    <li>Identify the different types of tissues and their characteristics.</li>
                    <li>Master various histological techniques, including tissue preparation, processing, and staining.</li>
                    <li>Apply histopathological knowledge in the diagnosis and classification of diseases.</li>
                    <li>Recognize the importance of histopathology in research and clinical practice.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </header>

        <nav class="module-list">
            <h2>Course Modules</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module1.html">
                        <h3>Module 1: Introduction and Importance of Histopathology</h3>
                        <p>This module defines histology and histopathology, explains their importance, and introduces basic histological techniques.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1 hour</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module2.html">
                        <h3>Module 2: Tissue Preparation Methods</h3>
                        <p>This module describes the fresh and fixed methods of tissue preparation.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1 hour</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module3.html">
                        <h3>Module 3: Methods of Examination of Tissues</h3>
                        <p>This module explains various techniques for examining tissues, including dissociation, smear technique, and sectioning.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1 hour</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module4.html">
                        <h3>Module 4: Specimen Collection and Transport</h3>
                        <p>This module outlines the procedures for collecting and transporting tissue specimens.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1 hour</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module5.html">
                        <h3>Module 5: Tissue Reception, Labeling and Fixation</h3>
                        <p>This module covers the procedures for receiving, labeling, and fixing tissue specimens.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1 hour</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module6.html">
                        <h3>Module 6: Post Mortem Changes and Functions of Fixatives</h3>
                        <p>This module describes post-mortem changes in tissues and explains the functions and qualities of fixatives.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1.5 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module7.html">
                        <h3>Module 7: Action of Fixatives and Factors Affecting Fixation</h3>
                        <p>This module details the action of fixatives and the factors that affect the fixation process.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1.5 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module8.html">
                        <h3>Module 8: Classification and Types of Fixatives</h3>
                        <p>This module classifies fixatives and describes various simple fixatives.</p>
                        <span class="duration">2 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module9.html">
                        <h3>Module 9: Fixation of Gross Specimen and Simple Fixatives (Formaldehyde)</h3>
                        <p>This module outlines the procedures for fixing gross specimens and provides a detailed description of formaldehyde as a fixative.</p>
                        <span class="duration">2 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module10.html">
                        <h3>Module 10: Post Fixation Treatment and Artefacts</h3>
                        <p>This module covers post-fixation treatments and describes various types of artifacts.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1.5 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="modules/module11.html">
                        <h3>Module 11: Post Chroming and Removal of Fixation Pigments</h3>
                        <p>This module explains post-chroming and post-mordanting techniques and describes how to remove fixation pigments.</p>
                        <span class="duration">1.5 hours</span>
                    </a>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </nav>

        <footer class="course-footer">
            <section class="prerequisites">
                <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
                <ul>
                    <li>Basic knowledge of biology and human anatomy</li>
                    <li>Familiarity with laboratory procedures</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </footer>
    </article>
</body>
</html>

    